title: Untitled
content:
-- zombie head = up
-- creeper head = down
local downStr = "minecraft:creeper_head"
local upStr = "minecraft:zombie_head"

local function moveUp()
	local success, data = turtle.inspect()
	if data.name == downStr then
		return false, "Done moving"
	else
		return turtle.up()
	end
end

local function moveDown()
	local success, data = turtle.inspect()
	if data.name == upStr then
		return false, "Done moving"
	else
		return turtle.down()
	end
end

local function main(...)
	print("Starting...")
	local success, data = turtle.inspect()
	if not success and not (data.name == upStr or data.name == downStr) then
		print("Please start me next to a creeper head to go down, or zombie head to go up")
	else
		if data.name == upStr then
			print("moving up")
			local success = moveUp()
			while success do
				success = moveUp()
			end
		else
			if data.name == downStr then
				print("moving down")
				local success = moveDown()
				while success do
					success = moveDown()
				end
			end
		end
	end
	print("done")
end

main(...)
